subsection.def:
ship
          (船、船舶) means a Hong
        Kong ship;

paragraph.content:
there is loss of life or major injury to any person on
                                        board, or any person is lost or missing from, a ship or a
                                        ship’s boat;

the date on which the seafarer left the ship;
                                                (L.N. 75 of
                                                2016)

all such property of which the master has taken charge
                                        pursuant to section 15(3) of the Repatriation
                                        Regulation specifying each item of such property;

each article forming part of such property sold
                                        pursuant to section 15(4)(a) of the Repatriation
                                        Regulation, and the price received for it;

may be unfit to discharge his duties, whether by reason
                                        of incompetency or misconduct or for any other
                                        reason;

subparagraph.content:
if the death or loss does not take place in or from
                                            the ship or in or from a ship’s boat, the place of
                                            death;

paragraph.content:
if the offence is not to be dealt with by the master,
                                        of the name of the officer authorized under section
                                            6(2) of the Disciplinary Offences Regulation to
                                        exercise the powers and duties of the master in respect of
                                        that offence;

that the master or the officer referred to in
                                        subparagraph (a) has read the charge to the
                                        seafarer;

subparagraph.content:
informed the seafarer of his rights under
                                                  section 9 of that Regulation;
                                                and

paragraph.content:
the density of the water in which the ship was when the
                                        particulars referred to in subparagraph (a) were
                                        taken;

subparagraph.content:
the density of the water in which the ship was
                                                when the particulars referred to in subparagraph (a)
                                                were taken;

the weight of fuel, water and stores required
                                                for consumption before the ship reaches salt water;
                                                and

paragraph.content:
the times of the opening and closing of any watertight
                                        door pursuant to regulation 4(1)(c) of the
                                        Closing of Openings Regulations;
